.\" Man page for hsh - Holberton School simple shell
.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "Holberton School" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
hsh \- A simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ command ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command interpreter written in C as part of the
Holberton School curriculum. It replicates basic functionality of
.B /bin/sh
and supports both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.PP
In
.B interactive mode,
the shell displays a prompt
.B ($)
and waits for the user to type a command.
The command is executed and the prompt appears again.

.PP
In
.B non-interactive mode,
commands are passed via a pipe or file and executed without displaying a prompt.

.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are supported:

.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell. The shell will terminate and return the exit status
of the last command executed.

.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables to standard output.
Each variable is printed on its own line in the format NAME=VALUE.

.SH EXAMPLES
.B Interactive mode:
.br
$ ./hsh
.br
($) /bin/ls
.br
hsh main.c shell.c
.br
($)
.br
($) exit

.PP
.B Non-interactive mode:
.br
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.br
hsh main.c shell.c

.PP
.B Piping a file:
.br
$ cat commands.txt
.br
/bin/ls
.br
/bin/ls
.br
$ cat commands.txt | ./hsh
.br
hsh main.c shell.c
.br
hsh main.c shell.c

.PP
.B Invalid command error:
.br
$ echo "qwerty" | ./hsh
.br
./hsh: 1: qwerty: not found

.SH COMPILATION
To compile hsh, run the following command:
.PP
.B gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the exit status of the last command executed.
Returns 0 on success, or a non-zero value on error.

